The paper focuses on technical debt in software development, which is a software engineering (cs.SE) problem. The framework proposed in the paper is built on top of business processes, indicating a potential connection to cybernetics (cs.CY) and control theory (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the evaluation of the framework, which suggests a potential connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and social and information networks (cs.SI) for analyzing the results.
